𝗧𝗼𝗽-𝗱𝗼𝘄𝗻 𝗰𝗮𝘂𝘀𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗻
Consider A and B but B composed of the elements of A, eg B is flock of birds. Using local rules birds exhibit flocking behavior but at that point the geometrical configuration influences what individual birds do.
